WHATWG Encoding Standard and WHATWG encoding data

This package includes behavior and compact source data derived from the WHATWG Encoding Standard and
the WHATWG encoding repository for encoding labels, web-compatible label remapping, TextDecoder
compatibility expectations, and legacy single-byte encoding indexes used by the native decoder
tables.

Covered materials in this package include support data or behavior for `windows-1251`,
`windows-1252`, `iso-8859-5`, `koi8-r`, `IBM866`/`cp866`, and the web-compatible remapping of
labels such as `iso-8859-1`, `latin1`, `us-ascii`, and related aliases to `windows-1252`.

Source: https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/
Repository data: https://github.com/whatwg/encoding
Repository inputs used for table verification: `encodings.json`, `index-windows-1251.txt`,
`index-windows-1252.txt`, `index-iso-8859-5.txt`, `index-koi8-r.txt`, and `index-ibm866.txt`.
